    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nFiles that get opened and then closed do not update oldfiles. Even though the changes made in them _do_ get registered, it is not possible to use `<C-o>` or `g;` to jump back to those files or to jump to the last edited position in those files. But undo and redo work correctly with the previous changes and have no problem jumping to that last edited position.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim\n:e ~/.bashrc \n:bdelete\n:q\n\nnvim\n:oldfiles\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe file should be added on top of the oldfiles\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux 1.0\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.26.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\npacman / system package manager",
